http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Two-injured-as-explosives-go-off/article13978034.ece

Two people suffered injuries when explosives, allegedly stored to hunt wild boars, went off at Gujjenahalli in Kadur taluk on Saturday. The injured have been identified as Manjappa (60) and Lepaksha (35) of Gujjenahalli. The poachers used explosives to capture wild animals in forest areas.The Singatagere police said that the explosives went off when Rajanna, a resident of the village, was filling them in a container to be used while poaching. Lepaksha and Manjappa, who were near the spot, suffered injuries. The police have registered a complaint filed by Lepaksha.